The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are core topics in computer science and economics. The use of terms such as "mechanism design", "Bayesian incentive compatible", and "duality-based framework" suggest that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of the auction mechanism, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
